52.7	Guaranteed_minimum_income	Guaranteed minimum income	A basic income is granted independent of other income (including salaries) and wealth, with no other requirement than citizenship. This is a special case of GMI, based on additional ideologies and/or goals. While most modern countries have some form of guaranteed minimum income, a basic income is rare.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/3/35/Felix_Golden_Egg_1936.jpg/220px-Felix_Golden_Egg_1936.jpg
